		<profileDesc>
			<abstract>
				<p>One way to speed up reinforcement learning is to enable learning to happen simultaneously at multiple resolutions in space and time. This paper shows how to create a Q-Iearning managerial hierarchy in which high level managers learn how to set tasks to their sub-managers who, in turn, learn how to satisfy them. Sub-managers need not initially understand their managers&apos; commands. They simply learn to maximise their reinforcement in the context of the current command. We illustrate the system using a simple maze task .. As the system learns how to get around, satisfying commands at the multiple levels, it explores more efficiently than standard, flat, Q-Iearning and builds a more comprehensive map.</p>
			</abstract>
